tags.name: captive reinsurers
tags.notes:
A captive insurer operating as a direct insurer insures the risks of the group and purchases reinsurance on the commercial reinsurance market.

Reinsurance can informally be described as insurance purchased by an insurance company.

A reinsurance captive does not issue policies directly to insureds and typically operates on a nonadmitted basis. A reinsurance captive reinsures the risks insured by one or more fronting companies.
